        "id": 8972
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-13T21:39:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My bad, I somehow though this function was doing image to buffer transfer. Unprotected buffer to protected image copy is allowed from a protected context. In the docs below, every detail is listed and it doesnt have any constraints on src for a copy.\n\"If commandBuffer is a protected command buffer, then dstImage must not be an unprotected image\"\nhttps://www.khronos.org/registry/vulkan/specs/1.1-extensions/man/html/vkCmdCopyBufferToImage.html\n\nGrCaps::transferFromOffsetAlignment section done.",
      "parentUuid": "cac0c117_1de23405",
